\begin_layout Subsection*
Task 3:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family roman
\series medium
\shape up
\size normal
\emph off
\bar no
\strikeout off
\xout off
\uuline off
\uwave off
\noun off
\color none
Let us assume 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{b}$
\end_inset

is back EMF of the motor and J is the moment of inertia of the flywheel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $E_{b}=k\omega_{1}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
State equation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $V=iR+L\frac{di}{dt}+E_{b}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow\frac{di}{dt}=\frac{V}{L}-\frac{iR}{L}-\frac{k\omega_{1}}{L}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow\dot{i}=\frac{V}{L}-\frac{iR}{L}-\frac{k\omega_{1}}{L}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now considering the gear ratio is 
\begin_inset Formula $N_{1}:N_{2}$
\end_inset

 so the speed would be 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{1}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 Now, the torque developed by the motor is given by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $T_{1}=k_{m}i$
\end_inset

 [considering flux constant]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The torque transformed to flywheel side will be given by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $T_{2}=\frac{T_{1}N_{1}}{N_{2}}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
which is also given by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
T
\begin_inset Formula $_{2}=J\frac{d\omega_{2}}{dt}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{d\omega_{2}}{dt}=\frac{T_{1}N_{1}}{JN_{2}}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow\frac{d\omega_{2}}{dt}=\frac{k_{m}N_{1}i}{JN_{2}}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\Rightarrow\dot{\omega}_{2}=\frac{k_{m}N_{1}i}{JN_{2}}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

